(7564, 209, 'sections_0_layout_1_content', '<h5 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>INNA</strong></h5>\r\nAlex and I first met during my sophomore (his senior) year of high school when he transferred to my school in San Francisco. I’m still not quite sure who was “too cool” for who, but we never shared anything more than a brief “What’s up” down the halls. It also didn’t help that he was dating a fellow dance company member, so as obviously handsome and mysterious as he was, he was off limits!\r\n\r\nIt wasn’t until four years after we graduated that we reconnected on social media (so romantic, we know). He lived in San Diego, and I lived in San Francisco. Although we haven’t seen each other in years, he was quite the charmer over the phone, and Skyping with him instantly became the highlights of my day. We finally decided to meet halfway in Santa Barbara. Our first date was at a famous burger place where I thought it would I’d be more impressive if I ordered a salad instead of the burger I really wanted. As a rookie to this dating thing, I decided that commitments and trying to impress was just not for me and didn’t talk to Alex for the next 6 months. Persistent as he was, he moved back to San Francisco, and convinced me to go on another date. This time around, I was absolutely smitten. His sweet, funny, intelligent, and charismatic soul instantly became my other half that I knew I did not want to be without.\r\n\r\nSix years later, I find myself living in the most beautiful state, with two fur babies, a pet gecko, and the man of my dreams who loves me for me. For the last 6 years we have shared lots of laughs, cries, and burgers on the regular with no regrets. I could not be more grateful that our friendship was rekindled when our paths brought us back together as it did. I cannot wait to marry my best friend, teammate, and man of my dreams!'),
